text: The Swedish Pentecostal Movement () is a Protestant community. On 31 December 2011 it consisted of 463 congregations. Together they make up the Swedish pentecostalism movement. The movement came to Sweden by 1906-1907. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website Category:Pentecostalism Category:Protestantism in Sweden Category:1900s establishments in Sweden
